Flooding continues to be a serious problem in Guangdong, Hunan and Jiangxi Provinces  and in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
Yesterday, urban and suburban areas of Guangxi's Wuzhou city were flooded by the  Xunjiang River.
In Guangdong Province, the Beijiang River was at 14.72 meters, about 4.22 meters above  the danger mark, late yesterday, and the flood peak on the Xijiang River was reached  today.
Flooding in Hunan Province's Changsha from the Xiangjiang River has affected more the  300,000 residents and closed more the 400 factories and 5,000 shops.
Late last night, the flood peak passed through Jiangxi Province's capital, Nanchang. 
